<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=8433&amp;p=35759#p35759"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">juniper7 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Is the OS build 17133.73 the one that is not going to be released,<br />until MS fixes some kind of blocking bug, and who knows what else?......... <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /></div><br /><br />17173.73 is the &quot;middle&quot; update. It was released to all Insiders on April 10. The bug was found in 17134.1 (rs4 release), the subsequent one. That still has only been released to Insiders on fast track. Luckily I did not get it. So, I have only about 1/2 of the Spring Update, I guess. However, Classic Shell Menu is still working great for me at this time. From what I can find about 17134.1 is that it will just fixes the &quot;bug&quot; some people have in 17173.73, with no significant changes. So, I guess for those of us who are lucky enough to be running ok with 17133.73, we have dodged the bullet for another six months or so.<br /><br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">UPDATE</span> 04/20/2018  Just updated to Windows 10 Version 1803 (OS Build 17134.1 without any problems regarding Classic Shell Menu.  It had a pop up reminding me to configure to new OS - and it evidently worked. Spring Update is now complete, I guess  - congrats Classic Shell Menu!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2454">JohnBurns</a> — Thu Apr 19, 2018 6:06 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
