I presently have Classic Shell Start Menu installed without Classic Shell Explorer, Classic Shell IE, or Classic Shell Update. My current Windows installation is Windows 10 Version 1803 (OS Build 17133.73 (First part of the latest Spring Update put out April 10th). All is working fine with no problems.  <br /><br />My question is: Will Classic Shell Start Menu probably continue to work ok as long as CS Explorer and CS IE aren't installed? I have also not installed CS Update due to the current status of CS.  I realize we never know what MS might do in the future, but for now I hope I can stick with Classic Shell Start Menu and be relatively safe. Appreciate any comments or suggestions. Thanks.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2454">JohnBurns</a> — Thu Apr 19, 2018 11:04 am</p><hr />
